[SN]TITLE[SN]
Vincent Kompany: Man City would be 'stupid' to give up title chase

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Manchester City "would be stupid to forget their history" and not fight for the title, says Vincent Kompany.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
City lost 2-1 at home to title rivals Tottenham and lie in fourth, six points off leaders Leicester.
A contentious Harry Kane penalty gave Spurs the lead, before Kelechi Iheanacho equalised, but Christian Eriksen scored the winner late on.
"There is not a chance we will give up on the title. We have to improve," City captain Kompany told BBC Sport.
